ver-evolving exchange between Christian college campuses in the U.S., where missionaries train, and schools in Kenya, Uganda, and Tanzania. Providing real insight into the lives of school children in East Africa, this book charts a new course for understanding the goals on both sides and the global connections forged in the name of faith.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aAnthropology of religionzAfrica, East. 0aChristianity and culturezAfrica, East. 0aChurch and educationzAfrica, East. 0aChurch schoolszAfrica, East. 0aEvangelistic workzAfrica, East. 0aMissionariesxTraining ofzUnited States. 0aMissionsxEducational workzAfrica, East. 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477345440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804773454423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804773454.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles